## Genetic markers

Different markers tell different stories: need markers with appropriate resolution

* marker locations
   * <#gloss autosome>: biparentally inherited
   * <#gloss Y chromosome> (non-recombining region NRY): paternal
   * <#gloss mitochondrial>: maternal, rapidly evolving
* marker types
    * <#gloss single nucleotide polymorphisms> (SNPs)
	* <#gloss microsatellite> markers (repetitive, rapidly evolving)
	* <#gloss haplotypes>: nonrecombining, inherited as a unit  
(mitochondria, NRY, linked SNPs)

## Signatures of bottlenecks

* low variation among human populations,  
relative to among-species variation in chimps
* due to <#gloss population bottleneck(s)>
* equilibrium variation maintained by   
<#gloss mutation-selection balance>
* estimated low <#gloss effective population size> ($\\approx 10,000$) of *H. sapiens* at present! [@tenesa_recent_2007;@park_effective_2011]
    - assortative mating
    - reproductive skew
	- past bottlenecks
	
